### Hierarchy in UX design
Hierarchy is a visual design principle that orders ​elements on a page and ​highlights them by their importance  
Adjusting size and color  

** hierarchy refers to a group of ​elements that are organized in order of importance  
** emphasis is about making ​one element stand out from ​the other elements surrounding it  

eg.  
新闻浏览页，新闻标题 - 内容总结 - 正文（信息层级，通过字体大小控制）  

we always want to make it clear to the user ​where to focus first and what action to take.   
​Hierarchy helps point users to ​the first step they should take in their user journey.   
guides the user to ​the most important places on the page  

Accessibility annotations create a visual hierarchy ​by indicating the order that ​elements on a screen should be read  
